gobuster - Gobuster is a powerful reconnaissance tool used to brute-force directories, files, and subdomains that may be hidden on a web server.

NOTES
-----------------------------------------------------
Don't forget to set file extensions 

php    - PHP scripts
html   - Static web pages
txt    - Text files
js     - JavaScript files
json   - Configuration and API responses
xml    - Data and configuration files
bak    - Backup files
zip    - Compressed archives
tar    - Archived data
gz     - Compressed archived data
log    - Log files
asp    - Microsoft web applications
aspx   - Microsoft web applications
jsp    - Java-based web applications
config - Configuration files

-----------------------------------------------------

example use | gobuster dir -w wordlist.txt -u website.com

Common options
  -w wordlist.txt
  -u website.com/
  -x php,txt,html
  -o output.txt
  
  
  -q     | quite mode
  -k     | skips SSL certificate verification
  -b 404 | excludes specific HTTP status codes
  -t 50  | sets the number of concurrent threads

Modes options
  dir – Directory and file enumeration          | google.com/FOUND
  dns – Subdomain discovery                     | FOUND.google.com
  vhost – Virtual host discovery                | FOUND.google.com
  fuzz – URL and parameter fuzzing              | google.com/page?file=FOUND
  s3 – Amazon S3 bucket enumeration             | FOUND.s3.amazonaws.com
  gcs – Google Cloud Storage bucket enumeration | storage.googleapis.com/FOUND

Examples
  gobuster dir -u http://example.com -w wordlist.txt
  gobuster dns -d example.com -w wordlist.txt
  gobuster vhost -u http://example.com -w wordlist.txt
  gobuster fuzz -u http://example.com/FUZZ -w wordlist.txt
